Level 0 DFD (Context Diagram) - Theory
Purpose:
The Context Diagram provides a high-level view of the entire system, showing how it interacts with external entities without revealing internal processes.
Key Components in Your Diagram:
1. External Entities (Actors):

Security Analyst - Initiates analysis requests and receives reports/alerts
System Administrator - Manages system configuration and monitors status
DevOps Engineer - Monitors system performance and receives status information
Application Servers - Source of raw application logs
System Servers - Source of system-level logs
Alert Notification System - Receives and distributes alert notifications
Machine Learning Engine - Provides ML insights and detection rules

2. Central Process:

Log Analysis & Incident Response System - The single process representing your entire system

3. Data Flows:

Inputs: Analysis Requests, Config & Access Mgmt, Monitor Requests, Raw Logs, System Logs, Detection Rules, ML Insights
Outputs: Reports & Alerts, System Status, Status Info, Alert Notifications
